<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2026 13:26:55 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>澳大利亚海滩上有奇怪的球体被冲上岸。当局称它们可能是“太空球”——火箭中的空燃料容器</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/strange-spheres-washed-ashore-on-an-australian-beach-authorities-say-theyre-probably-space-balls-empty-fuel-vessels-from-a-rocket-180989082/</link><description>这些闪亮的物体——每个物体的大小大约是篮球的两倍——从 7 月 3 日开始出现。当局最初担心它们是危险的，但后来确定它们很可能是安全的太空垃圾。</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 21:15:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/strange-spheres-washed-ashore-on-an-australian-beach-authorities-say-theyre-probably-space-balls-empty-fuel-vessels-from-a-rocket-180989082/</guid></item><item><title>人们认为高大的树木更容易受到干旱的影响。但东南亚的这些高耸植物已经适应了有效地输送水</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/tall-trees-were-thought-to-be-more-vulnerable-to-drought-but-these-towering-plants-in-southeast-asia-have-adapted-to-move-water-efficiently-180989075/</link><description>一项新的研究发现，巨大的龙脑香树具有特殊的适应性，可以将水分输送到最高的树枝，这挑战了它们更容易屈服于干燥条件的假设</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 19:29:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/tall-trees-were-thought-to-be-more-vulnerable-to-drought-but-these-towering-plants-in-southeast-asia-have-adapted-to-move-water-efficiently-180989075/</guid></item><item><title>泰国铁器时代墓地发现一对 2000 年前的金戒指，其中一枚刻有印度文字</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-pair-of-2000-year-old-gold-rings-one-engraved-with-indian-script-was-discovered-in-an-iron-age-burial-ground-in-thailand-180989081/</link><description>该雕刻似乎引用了印度或吠陀占星学中的“吉祥”星座</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 19:19:19 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-pair-of-2000-year-old-gold-rings-one-engraved-with-indian-script-was-discovered-in-an-iron-age-burial-ground-in-thailand-180989081/</guid></item><item><title>这颗巨大的行星可能在其恒星死亡后幸存下来。詹姆斯·韦伯太空望远镜刚刚找到大气层</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-giant-planet-survived-the-death-of-its-star-the-james-webb-space-telescope-just-found-its-atmosphere-180989077/</link><description>对 WD 1856 b（一颗紧密围绕白矮星运行的气态巨行星）的新观测，为太阳在大约 50 亿年后死亡后木星和土星可能发生的情况提供了预览。</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 19:09:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-giant-planet-survived-the-death-of-its-star-the-james-webb-space-telescope-just-found-its-atmosphere-180989077/</guid></item><item><title>你能猜出纸莎草碎片或彩绘陶瓷的起源吗？一名大学生将大都会博物馆的开放访问数据库变成了在线游戏</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/can-you-guess-the-origins-of-papyrus-fragments-or-painted-ceramics-a-college-student-turned-the-mets-open-access-database-into-an-online-game-180989080/</link><description>如果您认为自己是一名艺术史爱好者，请通过 Anthropeum 来测试一下您的聪明才智。该游戏从大都会博物馆的开放获取档案中提取十张图像，并要求玩家识别每件文物的时间和原产地</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 17:09:01 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/can-you-guess-the-origins-of-papyrus-fragments-or-painted-ceramics-a-college-student-turned-the-mets-open-access-database-into-an-online-game-180989080/</guid></item><item><title>机器人蟑螂可以帮助寻找自然灾害的幸存者。新型潜水服让昆虫能够扩大水下搜索范围</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cyborg-cockroaches-could-help-find-survivors-of-natural-disasters-new-diving-suits-allow-the-insects-to-expand-their-search-underwater-180989066/</link><description>此前，研究人员制造了电子植入物来控制蟑螂的运动，以执行搜救任务。现在，他们制作了可提供氧气的 3D 打印套装，让这些生物能够在水下生存长达三个小时</description><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 16:01:10 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/cyborg-cockroaches-could-help-find-survivors-of-natural-disasters-new-diving-suits-allow-the-insects-to-expand-their-search-underwater-180989066/</guid></item><item><title>海洋保护协会摄影比赛中的 11 张野生动物照片展示了地球水域的奇观</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-11-wildlife-images-from-the-ocean-conservancys-photography-contest-showcase-the-wonder-of-earths-waters-180989069/</link><description>该非营利组织的年度竞赛以海豹、企鹅和鱼类为特色，以激发人们对世界海洋的关爱</description><pubDate>Mon, 06 Jul 2026 22:15:10 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-11-wildlife-images-from-the-ocean-conservancys-photography-contest-showcase-the-wonder-of-earths-waters-180989069/</guid></item><item><title>在加州科学中心举行新展览之前，以独特的垂直展示方式观看“奋进号”航天飞机</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-space-shuttle-endeavour-in-a-unique-vertical-display-before-its-new-exhibition-launches-at-the-california-science-center-180989073/</link><description>今年 11 月，洛杉矶新塞缪尔·奥辛航空航天中心的游客将看到“准备发射”的“奋进”号，配有火箭助推器和燃料箱</description><pubDate>Mon, 06 Jul 2026 19:21:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-space-shuttle-endeavour-in-a-unique-vertical-display-before-its-new-exhibition-launches-at-the-california-science-center-180989073/</guid></item><item><title>早期开花植物可能依赖恐龙吃它们的肉质果实并传播它们的种子</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/early-flowering-plants-may-have-relied-on-dinosaurs-to-eat-their-fleshy-fruits-and-spread-their-seeds-180989076/</link><description>根据火山灰保存的化石，这些被称为被子植物的植物开始产生相对较大、蓝莓大小的果实，比之前认为的要早数百万年</description><pubDate>Mon, 06 Jul 2026 19:12:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/early-flowering-plants-may-have-relied-on-dinosaurs-to-eat-their-fleshy-fruits-and-spread-their-seeds-180989076/</guid></item><item><title>一次新的探险将创建极地沉船的 3D 数字双胞胎，这些沉船与竞相前往南极的竞争对手探险家的航行有关</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-new-expeditiion-will-create-3d-digital-twins-of-polar-shipwrecks-tied-to-voyages-of-rival-explorers-who-raced-to-the-south-pole-180989074/</link><description>罗伯特·法尔肯·斯科特率领“特拉诺瓦”号探险船和欧内斯特·沙克尔顿率领“探索”号船探险队，但这两位探险家都未能在南极洲中心插上第一面旗帜</description><pubDate>Mon, 06 Jul 2026 17:44:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-new-expeditiion-will-create-3d-digital-twins-of-polar-shipwrecks-tied-to-voyages-of-rival-explorers-who-raced-to-the-south-pole-180989074/</guid></item><item><title>饥饿的科莫多龙如何让科学家们确定我们像霍比特人一样的小表亲可能根本没有那么聪明</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-a-hungry-komodo-dragod-led-scientists-to-determine-our-small-hobbit-like-cousins-probably-werent-that-smart-after-all-180989078/</link><description>新的研究表明，“弗洛勒斯人”可能并没有在弗洛勒斯岛上狩猎大型动物或使用火，这表明这种小脑物种并不像曾经假设的那样“行为先进”</description><pubDate>Mon, 06 Jul 2026 15:31:58 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-a-hungry-komodo-dragod-led-scientists-to-determine-our-small-hobbit-like-cousins-probably-werent-that-smart-after-all-180989078/</guid></item><item><title>观看今年年度天文摄影师大赛中捕捉宇宙奇观的十幅壮观图像</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-ten-spectacular-images-from-this-years-astronomy-photographer-of-the-year-contest-that-capture-the-wonders-of-the-universe-180989065/</link><description>竞赛入围名单上的这些照片揭示了我们头顶上非凡的天体，无论是在深空还是在离家较近的地方</description><pubDate>Mon, 06 Jul 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-ten-spectacular-images-from-this-years-astronomy-photographer-of-the-year-contest-that-capture-the-wonders-of-the-universe-180989065/</guid></item><item><title>人工智能生成的亚历山大·汉密尔顿在本周末于波士顿开幕的美国金融博物馆谈论经济学</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-ai-generated-alexander-hamilton-chats-about-economics-at-the-museum-of-american-finance-opening-this-weekend-in-boston-180989071/</link><description>该博物馆始于纽约，多年来一直没有永久展览空间，描绘了美国金融机构的历史和影响力</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Jul 2026 21:28:51 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-ai-generated-alexander-hamilton-chats-about-economics-at-the-museum-of-american-finance-opening-this-weekend-in-boston-180989071/</guid></item><item><title>科学家表示，他们已经制造出能够进食、生长和繁殖的细胞，使它们离从头开始构建生命又近了一步</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-say-theyve-made-cells-that-feed-grow-and-reproduce-bringing-them-one-step-closer-to-building-life-from-scratch-180989070/</link><description>人造细胞显示出许多生命特征，但它们无法形成所有必要的内部结构，也无法分裂很多代</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Jul 2026 19:53:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-say-theyve-made-cells-that-feed-grow-and-reproduce-bringing-them-one-step-closer-to-building-life-from-scratch-180989070/</guid></item><item><title>3D 打印为在英国哈德良长城附近的罗马堡垒中发现的古代游戏板赋予了新的生命</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/3d-printing-gives-new-life-to-an-ancient-game-board-discovered-at-a-roman-fort-near-hadrians-wall-in-england-180989064/</link><description>在罗马帝国，特别是在罗马不列颠，士兵和平民都喜欢策略游戏 Ludus Latrunculorum</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Jul 2026 19:45:54 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/3d-printing-gives-new-life-to-an-ancient-game-board-discovered-at-a-roman-fort-near-hadrians-wall-in-england-180989064/</guid></item><item><title>对马克·罗斯科迷人的色域绘画感到困惑吗？看看那些启发他的文艺复兴大师</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/puzzled-by-mark-rothkos-captivating-color-field-paintings-look-to-the-renaissance-masters-who-inspired-him-180989068/</link><description>在欧洲之行期间，这位美国画家对 15 世纪和 16 世纪的艺术家和建筑师如何设计他们的作品来唤起特定的感受产生了浓厚的兴趣</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Jul 2026 19:01:07 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/puzzled-by-mark-rothkos-captivating-color-field-paintings-look-to-the-renaissance-masters-who-inspired-him-180989068/</guid></item><item><title>美国最古老的黑人教堂、莱特兄弟故居和纽约医院均属于急需保护的美国遗产</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/oldest-black-church-wright-brothers-homes-new-york-hospital-american-heritage-treasures-in-urgent-need-of-preservation-180989058/</link><description>世界纪念碑基金会在其“不可替代的美国”名单中，选择了具有创新、创造力和灵性的濒临灭绝的历史遗址来宣传和支持，以纪念美国建国 250 周年。</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Jul 2026 17:54:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/oldest-black-church-wright-brothers-homes-new-york-hospital-american-heritage-treasures-in-urgent-need-of-preservation-180989058/</guid></item><item><title>一份档案发现变成了一张藏宝图，带领一名潜水员找到了一艘载有硬币和黄金珠宝的 17 世纪沉船</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-archival-discovery-became-a-treasure-map-leading-a-diver-to-a-17th-century-shipwreck-carrying-coins-and-gold-jewelry-180989063/</link><description>通过线索了解东印度公司一艘在锡利群岛附近沉没的船只上失踪的船长的最后安息地，查看找到的文物</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Jul 2026 17:45:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-archival-discovery-became-a-treasure-map-leading-a-diver-to-a-17th-century-shipwreck-carrying-coins-and-gold-jewelry-180989063/</guid></item><item><title>一项研究表明，地球可能是 2000 万种昆虫的家园，是之前认为的数量的三倍多</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/earth-might-be-home-to-20-million-insect-speciesmore-than-three-times-as-many-as-previously-thought-a-study-suggests-180989062/</link><description>最近的估计已达成共识，即我们的星球拥有大约六百万个物种。但新的研究表明这些数字可能被大大低估了</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Jul 2026 15:30:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/earth-might-be-home-to-20-million-insect-speciesmore-than-three-times-as-many-as-previously-thought-a-study-suggests-180989062/</guid></item><item><title>亚历山大·汉密尔顿的第一家国家银行彻底改变了美国经济。关闭多年后，费城地标作为博物馆重新开放</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/alexander-hamiltons-first-national-bank-revolutionized-the-us-economy-after-sitting-shuttered-for-years-the-philadelphia-landmark-reopened-as-a-museum-180989056/</link><description>美国独立战争后不久，美国第一银行这个颇具争议的想法被证明是有先见之明的。经过耗资 4300 万美元的改造后，游客现在可以参观这座历史悠久的住宅</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 21:30:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/alexander-hamiltons-first-national-bank-revolutionized-the-us-economy-after-sitting-shuttered-for-years-the-philadelphia-landmark-reopened-as-a-museum-180989056/</guid></item></channel></rss>